  "texts": [
    "the Splitting Conjecture for negative Einstein manifolds with symmetry [BL23b]):Proposition 3.7.",
    "Let (M, g, X) be an expanding Ricci soliton obtained from a solution (g B, ρ, h) to the twisted harmonic-Einstein equations (20) with trivial ρ.",
    "Then, (M, g) is isometric to the Riemannian product (B, g B) × (N, h) of a compact Einstein manifold and a nilsoliton.Proof.",
    "Since the action of π 1 (B) on 𝔫 is trivial, h: B → Sym 2 + (𝔫 *) is π 1 (B)-invariant.",
    "Hence, h descends to a harmonic map ȟ: (B, g B) → (Sym 2 + (𝔫 *), g sym), which must necessarily be constant [EL78, Paragraph 4.5]."
  ],
